{
  "texts": [
    "From these considerations, we see that the notion of strong non-surjectivity is useful, whenever we are not able to verify that the space X is a dual Banach space, which is the situation to which we wish to apply the developed theory.",
    "Indeed, recall the diagram in Figure 1.",
    "The desired application for the theory developed in this section is for X = P d, Y * = L ∞ and T = Em.",
    "However, since we are not able to assert that P d is a dual Banach space (cf.",
    "Remark 3.15 and Proposition 3.16), strong non-surjectivity does not necessarily follow from non-surjectivity."
  ]
}